      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I AM THE STORM (1) had enough speed to lead from a wider barrier before cruising home by 11.6m in a dominant fresh victory at Terang. Has won both attempts at this shorter distance, one of them here. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw so looks tough to catch. ODIN (9) was impressive in finding winning form here last week, leading before cruising home by close to 18m. Draws on the back row this time but is a player again with even luck. PERUN NZ (8) has been good from this row at his last couple, winning at this circuit and distance then working but sticking on last time. Go well again. KARTIARE (11) came from this barrier for a resuming win at this venue and has won when second-up before so could go on with it.",
